[normal]Reprisals, as with humanitarian intervention, are generally seen as prohibited uses of force under international law
[normal] since the UN Charter prohibited force in 1945
[normal]. In 1970 the UN General Assembly declared in a consensus resolution, commonly seen as part of the fabric of international law
[normal],
[normal] that reprisals were unlawful – UNGA Res 
[normal]2625 (1970), 
[normal]known 
[normal]as the Declaration on Friendly Relations
[normal]. This point was raised in the Syrian debate in Hansard
[normal] HC
